@startuml
!include _theme.puml
left to right direction

title Monitor — Architecture Overview
caption Real-time monitoring dashboard with SSE fan-out and CRITICAL alert flow

actor "Browser User" as User
component "Dashboard UI\nNext.js / React" as Frontend
component "Monitor Hook\nEventSource client" as UseMonitor

package "Spring Boot Backend\nJava 21 / Spring Boot 3.4.4" {
  component "SseController\nGET /api/events/stream" as SseController
  component "EventBus\nSSE fan-out + heartbeat" as EventBus
  component "KafkaConsumerService\nCDC consumer" as KafkaConsumer
  component "PollingService\nHealth checks" as Polling
  component "EmailService\n@Async CRITICAL alerts" as EmailService
  component "SecurityConfig\nHTTP Basic + HSTS + CSP" as Security
  component "RateLimitingFilter\nBucket4j per-IP" as RateLimit
}

database "Oracle XE\nLOG_TRAZA" as Oracle
queue "Kafka topic\noracle.SYSTEM.LOG_TRAZA" as Kafka
component "Kafka Connect / Debezium" as Debezium
cloud "SMTP / Groupwise" as Smtp

User --> Frontend : Open dashboard
Frontend --> UseMonitor : Start monitoring
UseMonitor --> SseController : EventSource /api/events/stream
SseController --> EventBus : Register SseEmitter
EventBus --> UseMonitor : SSE stream\ncomments + named events

Oracle --> Debezium : CDC changes
Debezium --> Kafka : Debezium envelope
Kafka --> KafkaConsumer : consume CDC event
KafkaConsumer --> EventBus : publish(DATA)
KafkaConsumer --> EmailService : sendCriticalAlert()\nif severity == CRITICAL

Polling --> EventBus : publish(INFRASTRUCTURE)
Polling --> EmailService : sendCriticalAlert()\nif target is DOWN
EmailService --> Smtp : Plain-text email

Security --> SseController : HTTP Basic auth
RateLimit --> SseController : rate-limits /api/**

note right of EventBus
Backend SSE contract:
- event name = event.type.toLowerCase()
- comments: :connected / :heartbeat
- domain events: data / infrastructure
end note

note right of UseMonitor
Frontend listens to named SSE events:
- infrastructure
- data
Connection state comes from EventSource.onopen/onerror.
end note
@enduml

